This code has been written for codility.com programmers challenges (Argon 2015)
Well, after it had ended, and I've not done it in 2 hours. It's still not 
precise, there should be a next version as soon as I get a chance to 
improve it.  

The task:
Find a longest slice of a binary array that can be split into two parts: in the left part, 0 should be the 
leader; in the right part, 1 should be the leader.
